    <section>
      <h2>What is GPGenius?</h2>
      <p>GPGenius is an intelligent GPA calculator aimed toward Silver Creek High School's students. It includes many unique features, geared to create an ideal user experience and ease of navigation. Silver Creek High School does not include weighted GPAs on a student's transcript, and it is therefore up to the student to manually calculate their own weighted GPA. This may become confusing if the student is taking multiple AP courses or has varying letter grades in them. GPGenius has the instantaneous ability to calculate both weighted and unweighted GPAs, equipped with an intelligent function to save a student's results and a form-submit feature for a streamlined Question-and-Answer process.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Instructions</h2>
      <li>Login with your Student ID.</li>
      <li>If you have previously used GPGenius and saved your scores, you have the option to view your last saved results or proceed to the calculator.</li>
      <li>Enter the amount of classes you wish to calculate the GPA for.</li>
      <li>Type in the name of each class for easier tracking.</li>
      <li>Select the precise letter grade for each class from the drop-down menus.</li>
      <li>Select the type of class you are taking from the drop-down menus.</li>
      <li>Repeat steps 4-6 for the number of classes you inputted.</li>
      <li>Click Calculate GPA to receive both your weighted and unweighted GPA.</li>
      <li>Optional: Click the Save GPA button to save your results to your ID. It will appear the next time you log in.</li>
    </section>
